“GATT 1994” means the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade 
1994  set  out  in  Annex  1A  to  the  World  Trade  Organization 
Agreement;

“participating interested parties” means those interested parties that 
have  indicated  their  interest  in  participating  in  an  investigation  in 
accordance with section 10;

(a)  reviewing  the  information  notified  to  the  Committee 
regarding  the  finding  of  serious  injury  or  threat  thereof 
caused by increased imports and the proposed measure;

(a)  at  least  one  year lapsed  since the date of imposition of the 
earlier  safeguard  measure  on  the  imports  of  that  product; 
